GPU Monitoring Exercise:


===============================================================================


0.) MAKE SURE YOU ARE IN AN INTERACTIVE IDEV SESSION and on a gpu node 
    (gh or gh-dev on vista)

    Start a session:

       idev            #wait for prompt, accept reservation for gpu

                       # If the reservation doesn't provide a gpu partition
       idev -p gh-dev  # then try to get a gpu node, and  don't accept reservation.

       cd remora/gpu

       module load remora
       export REMORA_PERIOD=1

1.) Build blas-type code 

     make 

2.) Make sure the program runs:

     ./bla

3.) run bla with a period of 1 second, and view/open the remora-*/GPU/gpu*html file
    on your laptop.

       remora ./bla


        cat remora_*[0-9][0-9]/gpu/gpu_*.html
              #copy and paste into file on your laptop. (call it gpu.html)

       ON LOCAL machine:

         ON MACS:       open gpu.html
         ON LINUX:   firefox gpu.html
         ON Windows: <click> gpu.html

